The paper discusses a method for probabilistic inference in a medical expert system, which suggests that it is likely to fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of Bayesian belief networks and probabilistic inference also suggests that it could be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The mention of aggregation and decomposition of nodes suggests that it could be related to databases (cs.DB) and social networks (cs.SI).
